-- 
Pattern Energy, Samsung Acquire Acciona Wind Farm in Ontario

-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 
2011-09-12T14:53:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/pattern-energy-samsung-acquire-acciona-wind-farm-in-ontario.html
Pattern Energy Group LP, a San
Francisco-based renewable energy developer, and  Samsung C&T
Corp. (000830)  bought a 180-megawatt wind farm in southern Ontario from
 Acciona SA. (ANA)   The Armow project will use turbine components produced by
 Siemens AG (SIE)  in Ontario, Pattern said today in a statement.
Construction is set to begin in 2013 and the wind farm, in
Kincardine township about 235 kilometers (146 miles) northeast
of Toronto, is expected to go into operation the following year.
Ontario Power Authority will buy its electricity. The price was
not disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in New York at 
 egoossens1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
